        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-02-21T18:25:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-02-21T18:25:00-05:00" n="167" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d167">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BE/2–2147: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative at the United Nations</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Austin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-02-21T18:25:00-05:00">February 21, 1947—6:25 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>186. UK prepared to make statement on US trusteeship agreement. Lawford (UK)<note n="1" xml:id="d167fn1">V. G. Lawford, Adviser on the United Kingdom
                        Delegation Staff.</note> told <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> on
                    Feb. 21 that Cadogan<note n="2" xml:id="d167fn2">Sir Alexander Cadogan,
                        Permanent British Representative to the United Nations.</note> would be
                    prepared to state the British position on the US draft trusteeship agreement on
                    former Japanese mandated islands at the <gloss target="#t_SC2">SC</gloss>
                    meeting on Feb. 25. He indicated unofficially that statement merely would
                    reaffirm Britain’s previously voiced opinion that action on the US proposal
                    should await the signing of the Japanese peace treaty.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Austin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
